{"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Related Documentation","identifiers":["https:\/\/www.pointfree.co\/collections\/composable-architecture"],"anchor":"Related-Documentation","abstract":[{"text":"The collection of videos from ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/www.pointfree.co"},{"text":" that dive deep into the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"development of the library.","type":"text"}]}],"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The Composable Architecture (TCA, for short) is a library for building applications in a consistent"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and understandable way, with composition, testing, and ergonomics in mind. It can be used in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI, UIKit, and more, and on any Apple platform (iOS, macOS, tvOS, and watchOS)."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Additional-Resources","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Additional Resources"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/pointfreeco\/swift-composable-architecture"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/pointfreeco\/swift-composable-architecture\/discussions","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/www.pointfree.co\/collections\/composable-architecture"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This library provides a few core tools that can be used to build applications of varying purpose and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"complexity. It provides compelling stories that you can follow to solve many problems you encounter"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"day-to-day when building applications, such as:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"State management","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"How to manage the state of your application using simple value types, and share state across"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"many screens so that mutations in one screen can be immediately observed in another screen."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Composition"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"How to break down large features into smaller components that can be extracted to their own,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"isolated modules and be easily glued back together to form the feature."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Side effects","type":"text"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"How to let certain parts of the application talk to the outside world in the most testable and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"understandable way possible.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Testing","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"How to not only test a feature built in the architecture, but also write integration tests for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"features that have been composed of many parts, and write end-to-end tests to understand how","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"side effects influence your application. This allows you to make strong guarantees that your","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"business logic is running in the way you expect.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Ergonomics"}]}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"How to accomplish all of the above in a simple API with as few concepts and moving parts as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"possible."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture"]}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Essentials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/DependencyManagement","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingTCA","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Navigation","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Performance","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/FAQ"],"anchor":"Essentials"},{"title":"Tutorials","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/MeetComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/BuildingSyncUps"],"anchor":"Tutorials"},{"title":"State management","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Effect","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Store","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/SharingState"],"anchor":"State-management"},{"title":"Testing","identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestStore","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingTCA"],"anchor":"Testing"},{"title":